25|$|As agreed between Israel and <b>the</b> <b>Palestinian</b> <b>Authority</b> in the Oslo Accords, Israel has {{exclusive}} {{control over}} the airspace. It can interfere with radio and TV transmissions, and <b>the</b> <b>Palestinian</b> <b>Authority</b> cannot engage in independent initiatives for operating a seaport or airport. The Accords also permitted Palestinians to construct an airport, which was duly built and opened in 1998. Israel destroyed Gaza's only airport in 2001 and 2002, during the Second Intifada.|$|E
